privatetech.name: privatetech
privatetech.description: The MIB module is for xxx Tech.

sw0657840Reboot.name: sw0657840Reboot
sw0657840Reboot.description: Reboot the system. Get this OID always return zero. 0 - do nothing 1 - Reboot without saving start 2 - Reboot with saving start

sw0657840BiosVsersion.name: sw0657840BiosVsersion
sw0657840BiosVsersion.description: Get the BIOS version of the system.

sw0657840FirmwareVersion.name: sw0657840FirmwareVersion
sw0657840FirmwareVersion.description: Get the firmware version of the system.

sw0657840HardwareVersion.name: sw0657840HardwareVersion
sw0657840HardwareVersion.description: Get the hardware version of the system.

sw0657840MechanicalVersion.name: sw0657840MechanicalVersion
sw0657840MechanicalVersion.description: Get the mechanical version of the system.

sw0657840SerialNumber.name: sw0657840SerialNumber
sw0657840SerialNumber.description: Get the Serial number of the system.

sw0657840HostMacAddress.name: sw0657840HostMacAddress
sw0657840HostMacAddress.description: Get the MAC address of the system.

sw0657840DevicePort.name: sw0657840DevicePort
sw0657840DevicePort.description: Get the quantity of ports that this system owns now.

sw0657840RamSize.name: sw0657840RamSize
sw0657840RamSize.description: Get the RAM size of the system.

sw0657840FlashSize.name: sw0657840FlashSize
sw0657840FlashSize.description: Get the flash size of the system.

sw0657840DhcpSetting.name: sw0657840DhcpSetting
sw0657840DhcpSetting.description: Get/Set DHCP status of the system. 0 - DHCP disable 1 - DHCP enable

sw0657840IPAddress.name: sw0657840IPAddress
sw0657840IPAddress.description: Get/Set the IP address of the system. You can't set this OID if DHCP status is enabled.

sw0657840NetMask.name: sw0657840NetMask
sw0657840NetMask.description: Get/Set the subnet mask of the system. You can't set this OID if DHCP status is enabled.

sw0657840DefaultGateway.name: sw0657840DefaultGateway
sw0657840DefaultGateway.description: Get/Set the default gateway of the system. You can't set this OID if DHCP status is enabled.

sw0657840DnsSetting.name: sw0657840DnsSetting
sw0657840DnsSetting.description: Get/Set the source of DNS server. You can't set this OID if DHCP status is disabled. 0 - manual, the DNS server is from manual setting 1 - auto, the DNS server is assigned by DHCP server.

sw0657840DnsServer.name: sw0657840DnsServer
sw0657840DnsServer.description: Get/Set the DNS server of the system.

sw0657840SystemCurrentTime.name: sw0657840SystemCurrentTime
sw0657840SystemCurrentTime.description: Get the current time of the system.

sw0657840ManualTimeSetting.name: sw0657840ManualTimeSetting
sw0657840ManualTimeSetting.description: Get/Set the system time of the device. The input format is 'Year/Month/Day/Hour/Minute/Second'. ex: 2004/1/1/12/34/25 means 2004/1/1 - 12:24:25 . The value range: Year : 2000 - 2036, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59, Sec : 0 - 59.

sw0657840NTPServer.name: sw0657840NTPServer
sw0657840NTPServer.description: Get/Set the NTP Time Server. You can use the IP address or domain name.

sw0657840NTPTimeSync.name: sw0657840NTPTimeSync
sw0657840NTPTimeSync.description: Sync time from NTP Server. Get this OID always return zero. Set the Time Server and Time Zone before doing time sync. Notice that time server must be correct! The value range (0|1): 1 - sync. 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840DaylightSavingTime.name: sw0657840DaylightSavingTime
sw0657840DaylightSavingTime.description: Get/Set the daylight saving time. The value range is between -5 and 5. (Unit: hour)

sw0657840DaylightStartTime.name: sw0657840DaylightStartTime
sw0657840DaylightStartTime.description: Get/Set the Start time of Daylight Saving. The input format is 'MM/DD/HH', and daylight saving start month can't equal end month. example: month/day/hour 10/01/00 month: 01~12, day: 01~31, hour: 00~23 .

sw0657840DaylightEndTime.name: sw0657840DaylightEndTime
sw0657840DaylightEndTime.description: Get/Set the End time of Daylight Saving. The input format is 'MM/DD/HH', and daylight saving start month can't equal end month. example: month/day/hour 04/01/00 month: 01~12, day: 01~31, hour: 00~23 .

sw0657840AccountNumber.name: sw0657840AccountNumber
sw0657840AccountNumber.description: Get the current account number(s) of the system.

sw0657840AccountTable.name: sw0657840AccountTable
sw0657840AccountTable.description: This is a list of SW0657840AccountEntry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840AccountNumber.

sw0657840AccountEntry.name: sw0657840AccountEntry
sw0657840AccountEntry.description: This is the Entry(s) for account information.

sw0657840AccountIndex.name: sw0657840AccountIndex
sw0657840AccountIndex.description: This is the index of the account entry.

sw0657840AccountAuthorization.name: sw0657840AccountAuthorization
sw0657840AccountAuthorization.description: This is the authorization of the account entry.

sw0657840AccountName.name: sw0657840AccountName
sw0657840AccountName.description: This is the username of the account entry.

sw0657840AccountPassword.name: sw0657840AccountPassword
sw0657840AccountPassword.description: This is the password of the account entry. The return value is always '********'.

sw0657840AccountAddName.name: sw0657840AccountAddName
sw0657840AccountAddName.description: This is the account name for adding operation.

sw0657840AccountAddPassword.name: sw0657840AccountAddPassword
sw0657840AccountAddPassword.description: This is the account password for adding operation. The return value is always '********'.

sw0657840DoAccountAdd.name: sw0657840DoAccountAdd
sw0657840DoAccountAdd.description: Add account name. OID sw0657840AccountAddName and sw0657840AccountAddPassword must be filled first. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - add account. 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840AccountDel.name: sw0657840AccountDel
sw0657840AccountDel.description: Delete account. The value is valid sw0657840AccountIndex(Can't delete administrator).

sw0657840GetCommunity.name: sw0657840GetCommunity
sw0657840GetCommunity.description: Get/Set the get-community of the SNMP.

sw0657840SetCommunity.name: sw0657840SetCommunity
sw0657840SetCommunity.description: Get/Set the set-community of the SNMP.

sw0657840TrapHostNumber.name: sw0657840TrapHostNumber
sw0657840TrapHostNumber.description: Get the number of trap hosts.

sw0657840TrapHostTable.name: sw0657840TrapHostTable
sw0657840TrapHostTable.description: A list of trap host entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840TrapHostNumber.

sw0657840TrapHostEntry.name: sw0657840TrapHostEntry
sw0657840TrapHostEntry.description: This is the entry information for trap host.

sw0657840TrapHostIndex.name: sw0657840TrapHostIndex
sw0657840TrapHostIndex.description: The index of the trap host entry.

sw0657840TrapHostIP.name: sw0657840TrapHostIP
sw0657840TrapHostIP.description: This is the IP of the trap host.

sw0657840TrapHostPort.name: sw0657840TrapHostPort
sw0657840TrapHostPort.description: This is the receiving-port number of the trap host.

sw0657840TrapHostCommunity.name: sw0657840TrapHostCommunity
sw0657840TrapHostCommunity.description: The community name for the trap PDU.

sw0657840EventNumber.name: sw0657840EventNumber
sw0657840EventNumber.description: Get the total number of alarm events.

sw0657840EventTable.name: sw0657840EventTable
sw0657840EventTable.description: This is a list of alarm event entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840EventNumber.

sw0657840EventEntry.name: sw0657840EventEntry
sw0657840EventEntry.description: This is the entry information for alarm event.

sw0657840EventIndex.name: sw0657840EventIndex
sw0657840EventIndex.description: This is the index of the alarm event entry.

sw0657840EventName.name: sw0657840EventName
sw0657840EventName.description: This is the alarm event name.

sw0657840EventSendEmail.name: sw0657840EventSendEmail
sw0657840EventSendEmail.description: Send email when alarm event is triggered.

sw0657840EventSendSMS.name: sw0657840EventSendSMS
sw0657840EventSendSMS.description: Send SMS when alarm event is triggered.

sw0657840EventSendTrap.name: sw0657840EventSendTrap
sw0657840EventSendTrap.description: Send trap when alarm event is triggered.

sw0657840EmailServer.name: sw0657840EmailServer
sw0657840EmailServer.description: This is the SMTP server for alarm event.

sw0657840EmailUsername.name: sw0657840EmailUsername
sw0657840EmailUsername.description: This is the Username of SMTP server.

sw0657840EmailPassword.name: sw0657840EmailPassword
sw0657840EmailPassword.description: This is the User Password of SMTP server.

sw0657840EmailUserNumber.name: sw0657840EmailUserNumber
sw0657840EmailUserNumber.description: The number of the email users that you want to send the alarm notification.

sw0657840EmailUserTable.name: sw0657840EmailUserTable
sw0657840EmailUserTable.description: This is a list of email user entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840EmailUserNumber.

sw0657840EmailUserEntry.name: sw0657840EmailUserEntry
sw0657840EmailUserEntry.description: This is the Entry information for email user entry.

sw0657840EmailUserIndex.name: sw0657840EmailUserIndex
sw0657840EmailUserIndex.description: This is the index of the email user entry.

sw0657840EmailUserAddress.name: sw0657840EmailUserAddress
sw0657840EmailUserAddress.description: This is the email address of the email user entry.

sw0657840SMSServer.name: sw0657840SMSServer
sw0657840SMSServer.description: This is the SMS server for alarm event.

sw0657840SMSUsername.name: sw0657840SMSUsername
sw0657840SMSUsername.description: This is the Username of SMS server.

sw0657840SMSPassword.name: sw0657840SMSPassword
sw0657840SMSPassword.description: This is the Password of SMS server.

sw0657840SMSUserNumber.name: sw0657840SMSUserNumber
sw0657840SMSUserNumber.description: The number of the SMS users that you want to send the alarm notification.

sw0657840SMSUserTable.name: sw0657840SMSUserTable
sw0657840SMSUserTable.description: This is a list of SMS user entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840SMSUserNumber.

sw0657840SMSUserEntry.name: sw0657840SMSUserEntry
sw0657840SMSUserEntry.description: This is the Entry information for SMS user entry.

sw0657840SMSUserIndex.name: sw0657840SMSUserIndex
sw0657840SMSUserIndex.description: This is the index of the SMS user entry.

sw0657840SMSUserMobilePhone.name: sw0657840SMSUserMobilePhone
sw0657840SMSUserMobilePhone.description: The SMS phone number of the SMS user entry.

sw0657840SaveStart.name: sw0657840SaveStart
sw0657840SaveStart.description: Save current configuration into flash memory (Save as Start Configuration). Get this OID always return zero. 1 - save. 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840SaveUser.name: sw0657840SaveUser
sw0657840SaveUser.description: Save current configuration into flash memory (Save as User Configuration). Get this OID always return zero. 1 - save. 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840RestoreDefault.name: sw0657840RestoreDefault
sw0657840RestoreDefault.description: Restore factory default configuration. Get this OID always return zero. 2 - restore default included default ip address. 1 - restore default without changing current ip address. 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840RestoreUser.name: sw0657840RestoreUser
sw0657840RestoreUser.description: Restore user configuration. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - restore. 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840ExportConfigName.name: sw0657840ExportConfigName
sw0657840ExportConfigName.description: Get/Set the export file path and name.

sw0657840DoExportConfig.name: sw0657840DoExportConfig
sw0657840DoExportConfig.description: Do export-config. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - export start section. 2 - export user-conf section.

sw0657840ImportConfigName.name: sw0657840ImportConfigName
sw0657840ImportConfigName.description: Get/Set the import file path and name.

sw0657840DoImportConfig.name: sw0657840DoImportConfig
sw0657840DoImportConfig.description: Do import-config. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - import start section. 2 - import user-conf section.

sw0657840PingTest.name: sw0657840PingTest
sw0657840PingTest.description: Set the host address that you want to ping and the system will return the test result.

sw0657840ClearLog.name: sw0657840ClearLog
sw0657840ClearLog.description: Clear system log. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - clear log. 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840UploadLog.name: sw0657840UploadLog
sw0657840UploadLog.description: Upload current system log. Set the correct tftp server first. The format of log file is 'ModelName_SerialNumbuer_YYMMDD_HHMM'. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - upload log 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840AutoUploadLogState.name: sw0657840AutoUploadLogState
sw0657840AutoUploadLogState.description: Enable auto-upload log function. Set the correct tftp server first. The format of log file is 'ModelName_SerialNumbuer_YYMMDD_HHMM'. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - Enable auto-upload 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840LogNumber.name: sw0657840LogNumber
sw0657840LogNumber.description: Get the number of current system log.

sw0657840LogTable.name: sw0657840LogTable
sw0657840LogTable.description: This is a list of log entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840LogNumber.

sw0657840LogEntry.name: sw0657840LogEntry
sw0657840LogEntry.description: This is the Entry information for system log.

sw0657840LogIndex.name: sw0657840LogIndex
sw0657840LogIndex.description: This is the index of the log entry.

sw0657840LogEvent.name: sw0657840LogEvent
sw0657840LogEvent.description: This is the detail information of the log entry.

sw0657840FirmwareFileName.name: sw0657840FirmwareFileName
sw0657840FirmwareFileName.description: Get/Set the path and filename for firmware upgrading.

sw0657840DoFirmwareUpgrade.name: sw0657840DoFirmwareUpgrade
sw0657840DoFirmwareUpgrade.description: Do firmware upgrade. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - do firmware upgrade. 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840PortStatusTable.name: sw0657840PortStatusTable
sw0657840PortStatusTable.description: This is a list of port status entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840PortStatusNumber.

sw0657840PortStatusEntry.name: sw0657840PortStatusEntry
sw0657840PortStatusEntry.description: This is the entry(s) for port status information.

sw0657840PortStatusIndex.name: sw0657840PortStatusIndex
sw0657840PortStatusIndex.description: This is the index of the port status entry.

sw0657840PortStatusMedia.name: sw0657840PortStatusMedia
sw0657840PortStatusMedia.description: The port media type of the port status entry.

sw0657840PortStatusLink.name: sw0657840PortStatusLink
sw0657840PortStatusLink.description: This is the port link of the port status entry.

sw0657840PortStatusPortState.name: sw0657840PortStatusPortState
sw0657840PortStatusPortState.description: This is the port state of the port status entry.

sw0657840PortStatusAutoNego.name: sw0657840PortStatusAutoNego
sw0657840PortStatusAutoNego.description: This is the auto negotiation of the port status entry.

sw0657840PortStatusSpdDpx.name: sw0657840PortStatusSpdDpx
sw0657840PortStatusSpdDpx.description: This is the speed/duplex of the port status entry.

sw0657840PortStatusFlwCtrl.name: sw0657840PortStatusFlwCtrl
sw0657840PortStatusFlwCtrl.description: This is the flow control of the port status entry.

sw0657840PortStatuDescription.name: sw0657840PortStatuDescription
sw0657840PortStatuDescription.description: This is the description of port.

sw0657840PortConfNumber.name: sw0657840PortConfNumber
sw0657840PortConfNumber.description: Get the number of port configuration.

sw0657840PortConfTable.name: sw0657840PortConfTable
sw0657840PortConfTable.description: This is a list of port configuration entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840PortConfNumber.

sw0657840PortConfEntry.name: sw0657840PortConfEntry
sw0657840PortConfEntry.description: This is the Entry(s) for port configuration information.

sw0657840PortConfIndex.name: sw0657840PortConfIndex
sw0657840PortConfIndex.description: This is the index of the port configuration entry.

sw0657840PortConfPortState.name: sw0657840PortConfPortState
sw0657840PortConfPortState.description: This is the port state of the port configuration entry. 0 - disabled. 1 - enabled.

sw0657840PortConfSpdDpx.name: sw0657840PortConfSpdDpx
sw0657840PortConfSpdDpx.description: This is the speed/duplex of the port configuration entry. 0 - auto. 1 - 10M/Half. 2 - 10M/Full. 3 - 100M/Half. 4 - 100M/Full. 5 - 1G/Full.

sw0657840PortConfFlwCtrl.name: sw0657840PortConfFlwCtrl
sw0657840PortConfFlwCtrl.description: This is the flow control of the port configuration entry. 0 - disabled. 1 - enabled.

sw0657840PortConfDescription.name: sw0657840PortConfDescription
sw0657840PortConfDescription.description: This is the description of port.

sw0657840MirrorMode.name: sw0657840MirrorMode
sw0657840MirrorMode.description: Get/Set the Mirror mode. 0 - disabled. 1 - rx enable.

sw0657840MirroringPort.name: sw0657840MirroringPort
sw0657840MirroringPort.description: Get/Set the mirroring port. The port range is from 1 to 24.

sw0657840MirroredPorts.name: sw0657840MirroredPorts
sw0657840MirroredPorts.description: Get/Set the monitored ports. The port range is from 1 to 24, and the syntax is 1,5-7.

sw0657840MaxPktLenPortNumber.name: sw0657840MaxPktLenPortNumber
sw0657840MaxPktLenPortNumber.description: Get the number of Max. packet length.

sw0657840MaxPktLenConfTable.name: sw0657840MaxPktLenConfTable
sw0657840MaxPktLenConfTable.description: This is a list of Max. packet length entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840MaxPktLenPortNumber.

sw0657840MaxPktLenConfEntry.name: sw0657840MaxPktLenConfEntry
sw0657840MaxPktLenConfEntry.description: Entry(s) for Max. packet length information.

sw0657840MaxPktLenConfIndex.name: sw0657840MaxPktLenConfIndex
sw0657840MaxPktLenConfIndex.description: This is the index of the Max. packet length entry.

sw0657840MaxPktLenConfSetting.name: sw0657840MaxPktLenConfSetting
sw0657840MaxPktLenConfSetting.description: Get/Set the Max. packet length. The Max. packet length is 1518,1532,or 9216.

sw0657840BandwidthPortNumber.name: sw0657840BandwidthPortNumber
sw0657840BandwidthPortNumber.description: Get the number of bandwidth management configuration.

sw0657840BandwidthConfTable.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfTable
sw0657840BandwidthConfTable.description: This is a list of bandwidth management configuration entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840BandwidthPortNumber.

sw0657840BandwidthConfEntry.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfEntry
sw0657840BandwidthConfEntry.description: This is the Entry(s) for bandwidth management configuration information.

sw0657840BandwidthConfIndex.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfIndex
sw0657840BandwidthConfIndex.description: This is the index of the bandwidth management configuration entry.

sw0657840BandwidthConfIngressState.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfIngressState
sw0657840BandwidthConfIngressState.description: The ingress state of the bandwidth management configures entry. 0 - disabled. 1 - enabled.

sw0657840BandwidthConfIngressBW.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfIngressBW
sw0657840BandwidthConfIngressBW.description: Get/Set the ingress rate of the bandwidth management configuration. The ingress rate is from 0 to 1000.

sw0657840BandwidthConfStormState.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfStormState
sw0657840BandwidthConfStormState.description: The storm state of the bandwidth management configuration entry. 0 - disabled. 1 - enabled.

sw0657840BandwidthConfStormBW.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfStormBW
sw0657840BandwidthConfStormBW.description: Get/Set the storm rate of the bandwidth management configuration. The storm rate is from 0 to 1000.

sw0657840BandwidthConfEgressState.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfEgressState
sw0657840BandwidthConfEgressState.description: The egress state of the bandwidth management configuration entry. 0 - disabled. 1 - enabled.

sw0657840BandwidthConfEgressBW.name: sw0657840BandwidthConfEgressBW
sw0657840BandwidthConfEgressBW.description: Get/Set the egress rate of the bandwidth management configuration. The egress rate is from 0 to 1000.

sw0657840LoopDetectedNumber.name: sw0657840LoopDetectedNumber
sw0657840LoopDetectedNumber.description: Get the number of loop detected entry.

sw0657840LoopDetectedTable.name: sw0657840LoopDetectedTable
sw0657840LoopDetectedTable.description: A list of loop detected entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840LoopDetectedNumber.

sw0657840LoopDetectedfIndex.name: sw0657840LoopDetectedfIndex
sw0657840LoopDetectedfIndex.description: The index of the loop detected entry.

sw0657840LoopDetectedStateEbl.name: sw0657840LoopDetectedStateEbl
sw0657840LoopDetectedStateEbl.description: The state of the loop detected entry. 0 - disabled. 1 - enabled.

sw0657840LoopDetectedCurrentStatus.name: sw0657840LoopDetectedCurrentStatus
sw0657840LoopDetectedCurrentStatus.description: The current status of the loop detected port. 0 - unlocked 1 - locked due to the loop condition

sw0657840LoopDetectedResumed.name: sw0657840LoopDetectedResumed
sw0657840LoopDetectedResumed.description: Unlock the port which is locked due to loop condition. Get this OID always return zero. 1 - unlock the port, 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840LoopDetectedAction.name: sw0657840LoopDetectedAction
sw0657840LoopDetectedAction.description: Set the corresponding action while loop is detected. 1 - lock the loop port, 0 - do nothing.

sw0657840SFPInfoNumber.name: sw0657840SFPInfoNumber
sw0657840SFPInfoNumber.description: Get the number of sfp info entry.

sw0657840SFPInfoTable.name: sw0657840SFPInfoTable
sw0657840SFPInfoTable.description: A list of sfp info entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of sw0657840SFPInfoNumber.

sw0657840SFPInfoIndex.name: sw0657840SFPInfoIndex
sw0657840SFPInfoIndex.description: The index of the sfp info entry.

sw0657840SFPConnectorType.name: sw0657840SFPConnectorType
sw0657840SFPConnectorType.description: Get connector type of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPFiberType.name: sw0657840SFPFiberType
sw0657840SFPFiberType.description: Get fiber type of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPWavelength.name: sw0657840SFPWavelength
sw0657840SFPWavelength.description: Get tx central wavelength of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPBaudRate.name: sw0657840SFPBaudRate
sw0657840SFPBaudRate.description: Get baud rate of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPVendorOUI.name: sw0657840SFPVendorOUI
sw0657840SFPVendorOUI.description: Get vendor OUI of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPVendorName.name: sw0657840SFPVendorName
sw0657840SFPVendorName.description: Get vendor name of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPVendorPN.name: sw0657840SFPVendorPN
sw0657840SFPVendorPN.description: Get vendor part number of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPVendorRev.name: sw0657840SFPVendorRev
sw0657840SFPVendorRev.description: Get vendor revision number of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPVendorSN.name: sw0657840SFPVendorSN
sw0657840SFPVendorSN.description: Get vendor serial number of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPDateCode.name: sw0657840SFPDateCode
sw0657840SFPDateCode.description: Get data code of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPTemperature.name: sw0657840SFPTemperature
sw0657840SFPTemperature.description: Get current temperature of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPVcc.name: sw0657840SFPVcc
sw0657840SFPVcc.description: Get current internal supply voltage of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPTxBias.name: sw0657840SFPTxBias
sw0657840SFPTxBias.description: Get current TX Bias of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPTxPWR.name: sw0657840SFPTxPWR
sw0657840SFPTxPWR.description: Get current TX output power of the sfp.

sw0657840SFPRxPWR.name: sw0657840SFPRxPWR
sw0657840SFPRxPWR.description: Get current Received Power of the sfp.

sw0657840ModuleInserted.name: sw0657840ModuleInserted
sw0657840ModuleInserted.description: Send the trap when a module is inserted to the system. The OID value means the port number.

sw0657840ModuleRemoved.name: sw0657840ModuleRemoved
sw0657840ModuleRemoved.description: Send the trap when a module is removed from the system. The OID value means the port number.

sw0657840DualMediaSwapped.name: sw0657840DualMediaSwapped
sw0657840DualMediaSwapped.description: Send the trap when the dual media port changed. The OID value means the port number.

sw0657840LoopDetected.name: sw0657840LoopDetected
sw0657840LoopDetected.description: Send the trap when loop condition has been detected. The OID value means the port number.

sw0657840StpStateDisabled.name: sw0657840StpStateDisabled
sw0657840StpStateDisabled.description: Send the trap when the operational state of STP is from enabled to disabled.

sw0657840StpStateEnabled.name: sw0657840StpStateEnabled
sw0657840StpStateEnabled.description: Send the trap when the operational state of STP is from disabled to enabled.

sw0657840StpTopologyChanged.name: sw0657840StpTopologyChanged
sw0657840StpTopologyChanged.description: Send the trap when RSTP determines a port should enter the FORWARDING state (a topology change occurs). The OID value is the ifIndex of the port that produces the topology change.

sw0657840LacpStateDisabled.name: sw0657840LacpStateDisabled
sw0657840LacpStateDisabled.description: Send the trap when the operational state of LACP is from enabled to disabled. The OID value means the disabled Group ID.

sw0657840LacpStateEnabled.name: sw0657840LacpStateEnabled
sw0657840LacpStateEnabled.description: Send the trap when the operational state of LACP is from disabled to enabled. The OID value means the disabled Group ID.

sw0657840LacpPortAdded.name: sw0657840LacpPortAdded
sw0657840LacpPortAdded.description: Send the trap when the state of port is in 'trunk ready'.

sw0657840LacpPortTrunkFailure.name: sw0657840LacpPortTrunkFailure
sw0657840LacpPortTrunkFailure.description: Send the trap when one port is not able to be aggregated due to duplex-mode of the port.

sw0657840GvrpStateDisabled.name: sw0657840GvrpStateDisabled
sw0657840GvrpStateDisabled.description: Send the trap when the operational state of GVRP is from enabled to disabled.

sw0657840GvrpStateEnabled.name: sw0657840GvrpStateEnabled
sw0657840GvrpStateEnabled.description: Send the trap when the operational state of LACP is from disabled to enabled.
